|Comments=We have three schemas for democracy as of now, one is dimukrasi, the Western loanword, the second is ardum-salari, the Persian neologism that closely approximates the concept of democracy, and the last is mardum-salari-i dini, or the concept of religous democracy based on Islamic values and principles. Perhas, one could argue that the last notion is distinct enough in the Persian conext to warrn its separate existence but the other two are used interchangably. We need to discuss in our next meeting whether we would like to keep the first two together or merge them
