|Cultural information=In the political discourse of the Islamic Republic, a term that has also gained currency in recent years is mardum-sālāri-yi dini (religious democracy). This concept gives precedence to Divine ruling; the interests of the masses are determined by the representatives of the Divine rule (positions not elected by the people include the office of the Ayatollah and members of the Guardianship of Islamic Jurists), a select number of these representatives (President, members of the Iranian majlis, etc) are elected by the people. The concept of religious democracy is being further investigated.
